r palaces turn into the abysses\r\nGray -haired Atlantic, like a city of noisy waters, -\r\nFrom the depths your call will reach, your call one,\r\nIn the millennium, your voice will cross. The nurses of Asia, and you, sons of the East,\r\nAnd new tribes of Australia and two\r\nAmerica, you shine, an unfading eye,\r\nYou are burning, in old age, not an erased spirit! And I, your lesser son, and I, your guest is uninvited.\r\nI am happy that I saw you in the shrine,\r\nLet them get stronger, let your holy countries bloom\r\nIn the name of the general bliss of being!	Брюсов Валерий Яковлевич	https://poemata.ru/poets/bryusov-valeriy/ya-v-more-ne-iskal-tainstvennyh-utopiy/	0	2023-01-20 07:05:19.242432
