n\r\nThat all this will not last long. Everything is mixed: the sea and you,\r\nAll your sadness, mystery and charm,\r\nAnd unknown shape flowers,\r\nAnd herbs of fading charm. In every word of your word - nightingales\r\nThey sang, fluttered wings.\r\nThere were your lips,\r\nYour hair fell low ... Again the sea.And again Bela\r\nThe edge of the foam.And this is eagerly.\r\nYou were?Was it really?\r\nOr not?This is unknown to me.	Ахмадулина Белла	https://poemata.ru/poets/ahmadulina-bella/gagra/	0	2024-08-16 23:35:20.65896
